  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (software-fault gap probe)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The solver pipeline is implemented as a multi-threaded RANS CFD code with a coupled hemolysis transport sub-model; validation activities confirmed nominal solution delivery across all five operating points but did not exercise software-fault modes.",
